🔹 1. Academic Module (Highest Priority)

This is your foundation.

📊 Attendance tracking (faculty + student view)
📚 Subject materials (PDFs, notes, links)
📄 PYQ Papers (with filters: branch, year, subject)
🧾 Course structure (syllabus view)
🎓 Open elective selection

👉 Redirect idea: You can link existing website pages here (good shortcut)

🔹 2. Student Services Module

Handles student interaction & communication.

📢 Notifications (admin → students)
📰 News bulletin
📝 Student feedback system
⚠️ Grievance system (ticket-based)

💡 Tip: Build grievance like:

Ticket ID
Status (Pending / In Progress / Resolved)
🔹 3. Campus Utility Module

Useful daily-life features.

🗺️ College map (embed Google Maps or custom map)
🚌 Transportation routes & bus tracking (basic version = routes + timing)
🏫 Admission process guide (static content)
🔹 4. Community & Engagement Module

This is what makes your app stand out.

🛒 Student marketplace (buy/sell items)
🎉 Event hosting (clubs can create events)
👥 Student clubs (pages + membership)
🔹 5. Admin Panel (VERY IMPORTANT)

Without this, your system won’t work in real life.

Manage students & faculty
Upload materials & PYQs
Approve marketplace listings
Post notifications/news
Handle grievances



Smart Features
📅 Academic calendar
⏰ Exam reminders
⭐ Social Layer
      Discussion forum (like mini Reddit for college)
      Like/comment system on posts